original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses the ANSI escape sequence for setting the foreground color to green. In this case, the code is "\033[32m", where "\033" represents the escape character and "[32]" specifies the green color code. Here's an example of its usage:

```
\033[32mThis text will appear in green.\033[0m
```

The "\033[0m" at the end resets the terminal to the default colors. Remember, this won't actually display green text until viewed within a compatible terminal emulator supporting ANSI escape codes.
